[SN]TITLE[SN]
Vandalised Markethill Primary School in Turriff to reopen

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An Aberdeenshire primary school forced to close for two days after vandals caused more than Â£20,000 of damage is to reopen on Wednesday.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Markethill School in Turriff was closed to pupils and staff on Monday and Tuesday.
Units were destroyed, food thrown about, and a valuable stained glass window destroyed at the weekend.
Aberdeenshire Council thanked everyone who had been involved in the clear-up operation.
